{
  "texts": [
    "Temporal Fusion Transformer (TFT) [33] integrates attention with static covariates and gating mechanisms for interpretability and multi-horizon forecasting, while N-BEATS [34] uses backward and forward residual links in a deep MLP architecture and performs strongly on benchmark datasets.",
    "Although these models achieve competitive performance in structured time series prediction, they are not designed to integrate unstructured financial news.",
    "Some recent efforts [45] attempt to combine text and price signals but do not explicitly capture intercompany sentiment spillovers.",
    "Our proposed Dual Transformer model addresses this gap through a two-stage architecture: the first Transformer encodes sentiment relationships across firms, and the second integrates this representation with historical price data for forecasting.",
    "This design enables richer modeling of multi-firm sentiment dynamics alongside temporal dependencies."
  ]
}